            <h4>FAQs</h4>

            <h5>How much does it cost to fly Air Canada business class?  </h5>
            <p>For the majority of domestic and international flights, the Air Canada Last Minute Upgrade Purchase is available online up to 24 hours before departure or in person up to an hour before departure. Depending on the travel path and time of year, upgrading to business class will cost anywhere from $300 to $1,000. </p>
            <h5>How many miles is it to upgrade to business class on Air Canada?  </h5>
            <p>Depending on the trip, travelers wishing to upgrade to Air Canada business class should budget between 15,000 and 50,000 Aeroplan Miles. Please take note that to be eligible for upgrades, you must purchase tickets in classes Y, B, or O.</p>
            <h5>Can I change the business class reservation I made on Faresmatch for Air Canada?  </h5>
            <p>If you wish to modify an Air Canada reservation that you booked using our site, there can be restrictions and refunds. Review the fare conditions and change policy before making any modifications. </p>
            <h5>Do business class chairs on Air Canada lay flat?  </h5>
            <p>Business class seats on all Air Canada widebody aircraft, including the Boeing 787-8, 787-9, 777-200, 777-300, and Airbus A330-300, are lie-flat.</p>
            <h5>What does Air Canada's business (p) mean? </h5>
            <p>By far the most common fare category is Air Canada Business (P). Specifically, the (P) denotes the Business Class (flexible) cost, which is free of charge for cancellations and marginally more expensive than the lowest business class fare.</p>


